## ⚡ Optional: Iterative Version (Even Better)

```java
public static int binarySearchIterative(ArrayList<Integer> arr, int target) {
    int left = 0;
    int right = arr.size() - 1;

    while (left <= right) {
        int mid = left + (right - left) / 2;

        if (arr.get(mid) == target) {
            return mid;
        } else if (arr.get(mid) > target) {
            right = mid - 1;
        } else {
            left = mid + 1;
        }
    }

    return -1;
}
```

---

## 🚨 Key Takeaway

Binary search is about **narrowing boundaries**, not shrinking arrays.

